b'As we continue celebrating #BlackHistoryMonth, a special #HighFiveFriday goes out to the #ArconicTennessee chapter of #AAHN. They\xe2\x80\x99ve been supporting their local chapter of Big Brother Big Sisters (@bbbsamerica) through volunteering and donations for several years, and recently welcomed BBBS Community Engagement Director Vivian Gwinn to the plant to speak about volunteer and mentorship opportunities.'

b'We asked continuous improvement engineer, Troy, from #ArconicRanchoCucamonga what advice he would give to the next generation of engineers. Troy said: "Take the time to learn as much as you can, not only in your department but in other departments as well. Spend time on the floor to match the data to reality." #NationalEngineersWeek #EWeek2019'

b'What makes Arconic a stronger team? Temi, metallurgical engineer at #ArconicLancaster and Communications lead for #AAHN, explains: \xe2\x80\x9cInclusive and diverse teams allow us to be more innovative, while creating opportunities for growth and exposure for those who wouldn\xe2\x80\x99t otherwise be in that position. These two things combined create an overall stronger workforce.\xe2\x80\x9d #BlackHistoryMonth #NationalEngineersWeek #eweek2019'

b'Throughout February we\xe2\x80\x99ll be highlighting members of the Arconic African American Heritage Network (#AAHN) who live our core values both in and out of the workplace. b'Go big or go home! As airplane wings get larger, our thick plate enables structural strength and stiffness, even for carbon fiber wings. b'Our shared passion for advancing the next frontier of defense and space made us the ideal partner for @lockheedmartin in developing advanced materials and manufacturing processes to support that mission. b'We\xe2\x80\x99re advancing space exploration with products for launch vehicles, propulsion, crew capsules and more. Our #3D printed parts for the Orion spacecraft\xe2\x80\x94on display at #FIA18\xe2\x80\x94are one example. #ThatsArconic'

b'#FIA18 #POTD: @lockheedmartin\xe2\x80\x99s #F35 Joint Strike Fighter displays impressive cutting-edge materials and next-generation avionics at #Farnborough. b"#DidYouKnow that Arconic is a vertically integrated supplier of #titanium seat track products? Join Technologist Ed Colvin inside the fuselage of our airplane display at #FIA18 to learn more about how our products are advancing the interior of today's aircraft. \n#wereonit"

b'Front to back and virtually everywhere in between, our full-size #jetengine model at #FIA2018 displays our tremendous technical expertise. Arconic can produce more than 90% of all structural and rotating engine components. \n#avgeek #aviation #Farnborough'
